{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c7a0c9be-6938-456e-9db3-f9e8f438e2ab","content":"**No, `net6.0` is not supported by MSTest v4.** MSTest 4.x dropped support for .NET 6.0 (which is already end-of-life). The minimum supported target frameworks are:\n\n- **`net8.0`** (or later)\n- **`net462`** (or later, for .NET Framework)\n\nYou'll need to update your `TargetFramework` to at least `net8.0` before upgrading to MSTest 4. For example:\n\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\nWould you like me to update the project to target `net8.0` and upgrade to MSTest 4?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"faacbf92-4f44-4570-90df-1166339210de","outputTokens":170,"requestId":"1BD2:2912D8:BD998A:D5F5CC:6A03F17C"},"id":"18a91086-46f7-49fe-a8a2-613b3a96d36d","timestamp":"2026-05-13T03:35:29.611Z","parentId":"87cc9854-4456-48bc-8dd4-b3236f656b47"}
